%% Diagram: Sale-day timeline (T0 = sale opens)
%% Type: gantt
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
gantt
    title Sale-day operational timeline (T0 = sale opens)
    dateFormat HH:mm
    axisFormat %H:%M

    section Pre-sale (T-60 to T-1)
    Pre-warm CDN with waiting-room HTML        :pre1, 09:00, 30m
    Deploy WAF rules + bot baselines           :pre2, 09:00, 30m
    Open pre-sale waiting room                 :pre3, 09:30, 30m
    Mint tokens / load inventory into shards   :pre4, 09:45, 15m

    section Sale open (T0)
    Randomise pre-sale arrivals                :crit, t0a, 09:59, 1m
    Sale opens (admission gate engaged)        :milestone, t0b, 10:00, 0m

    section Peak (T0 to T+5)
    Edge absorbs polling spike                 :p1, 10:00, 5m
    Token-gated admission to checkout          :p2, 10:00, 5m
    Atomic Redis decrement on hot SKUs         :p3, 10:00, 5m
    Inventory depletion (typical)              :milestone, p4, 10:05, 0m

    section Drain (T+5 to T+30)
    Outstanding reservations expire / restock  :d1, 10:05, 25m
    Async order workers drain queue            :d2, 10:00, 30m
    DLQ inspection + manual replays            :d3, 10:15, 15m

    section Post-sale (T+30+)
    Sale closed, waiting room shut down        :milestone, post1, 10:30, 0m
    Capture metrics + postmortem snapshot      :post2, 10:30, 30m
